In Sanskrit (Bhs. Sansekerta), Dasha means 10 and Svara means sound/music. Peacock is not only one of Indonesia's elegant birds, but it also symbolises integrity and beauty. The 10 beautiful feathers appreciate nine-achieved Soundsekerta events and also the 10th anniversary celebration for this year. Dashvara shows our desire to deliver an astonishing Soundsekerta 2016: A Decade to Remember.
